        "title": "Add native Japanese localization support",
        "body": "Reopens #1242 with the rebase on top of current main.\n\nThe previous PR (#1242) was force-closed because the head branch had to be force-pushed to bypass GitHub's email-privacy block on commits authored by other contributors (rebase onto `steipete/main` 0b7de584 dragged in 86 commits with private emails, which `yuxin/feat/add-japanese-localization` could not accept).\n\n## What's in this PR\n\nAdds `ja` as a first-class UI language (`AppLanguage.japanese = \"ja\"`), including:\n\n- `Sources/CodexBar/Resources/ja.lproj/Localizable.strings` — full Japanese translations (settings panes, about, menus, display labels, lower-section labels)\n- `Sources/CodexBar/PreferencesGeneralPane.swift` — `AppLanguage` enum + `label` switch updated to include Japanese\n- `Tests/CodexBarTests/PreferencesPaneSmokeTests.swift` — smoke test coverage for the new locale\n- Polish commits over the initial add: 5 commits total\n\n## Why a new PR\n\nPR #1242 was closed by GitHub when I force-pushed the head branch to reset its base onto `steipete/main` (the original PR's head was last based on `e7a96dc5`, ~3 weeks behind main, and the conflicts on the en/es/ca/pt-BR/sv/zh-Hans/zh-Hant `Localizable.strings` + `PreferencesGeneralPane.swift` had to be re-resolved). GitHub does not allow `state=open` on a PR whose head branch has been force-pushed after close, even by the same author — it must be re-opened as a fresh PR.",
